# Just make your life easy

after cloning project from GIT follow the next steps

- install all python modules

`pip install -r requirements.txt`

- create database and change database connetcion in settings.py


- migrate
`./manage.py migrate`

- create user admin
`./manage.py createsuperuser`


## Prepare initial data

- load elasticsearch settings
```commandline
./manage.py loaddata elastic_settings.json
```

- load attributes from elastic mapped fields
```commandline
/attribute/attribute_reload_mapped_attributes_list
```

- load entity attributes
```commandline
./manage.py loaddata entity_attributes.json
```

- define attributes for every entity_attribute, do it on url `http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/attribute/entityattribute/`

- load drawing models
```commandline
./manage.py loaddata init_graph_model_drawing.json
```


- load model templates
```commandline
./manage.py loaddata init_model_templates.json
```

- load relation templates
```commandline
./manage.py loaddata init_relation_templates.json
```
